SIMPLE: maul
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maul
<hw>Maul</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Mall</er> a
hammer.]</ety> <def>A heavy wooden hammer or beetle.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>mall</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maul</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Maul
<hw>Maul</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Mauled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Mauling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To beat and bruise
with a heavy stick or cudgel; to wound in a coarse manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Meek modern faith to murder, hack, and <qex>maul</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To injure greatly; to do much harm to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It <qex>mauls</qex> not only the person misrepreseted, but him
also to whom he is misrepresented.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maule</ent>⟦br⟧
